  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. This assessment evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. The intended use scope — steady-state CFD simulation of a centrifugal pump operating at 3–6 L/min flow rate and 2000–4000 RPM impeller speed, with the decision question being acceptability for pre-market submission to support worst-case operating point identification — is described fully in the Claim and Requirement nodes. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2).",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case-identification",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cpb-cfd-hemolysis-credible-for-worst-case-cpb",
